Description: Fragment of flattened handle of pottery transport amphora. Stamped on vertical face. Clay very fine grey-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. The stamp may be an Egyptian symbol, but the clay does not suggest local manufacture, being more akin to Chian (where we do not have flat handles).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ID.118)
